ce:section.ce:para:
This study employs an NCM pouch-type lithium-ion battery as the research subject. The cathode active material is nickel-manganese-cobalt oxide, while the anode active material is graphite. Active materials are coated on both sides of the current collectors, with a total of 24 layers of anode current collectors and 23 layers of cathode current collectors. Detailed parameters are provided in Table 1
                        . To investigate the swelling force characteristics of the lithium-ion battery under constant-gap constraints, a specialized fixture was first designed for swelling force testing. This fixture primarily consists of a spoke-type load cell (model: DYLF-102, measuring range: 0–300 kg), preload nuts, and steel plates. Subsequently, an experimental platform (Fig. 1
                        ) was developed to achieve precise current excitation control and synchronized acquisition of voltage, temperature, and swelling force responses. The platform integrates battery test system, thermal chamber, swelling force fixture, data acquisition unit, thermocouple and host computer. The sampling frequency of all experimental devices was set to 1 Hz. The voltage, current, swelling force, and temperature data were subsequently aligned based on absolute timestamps.
